                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#f28e2b' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Section 1: Key Business Insights (The &quot;What We Learned&quot;)</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#f28e2b' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Domain Expertise is Crucial:</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'> The engineered, high-level math equations (Features 22-28) provided significantly more predictive power than the raw sensor data (Features 1-21). </run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11' italic='true'>Insight: Investing in theoretical physicists to engineer features yields higher ROI than simply adding more raw sensors.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#f28e2b' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Proof of Concept Success:</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'> The PySpark pipeline successfully bypassed single-node memory limits, proving that a Big Data architecture can process complex collision data efficiently. The GBT model established a strong baseline accuracy of </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>69.67%</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'> using only a 5% data sample.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#f28e2b' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Section 2: Strategic Recommendations (The &quot;Next Steps&quot;)</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#f28e2b' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>1. Cloud Migration for Full Scale:</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'> To push the model&apos;s accuracy past the 70% threshold, it is highly recommended to migrate this exact PySpark codebase to a distributed cloud cluster (e.g., AWS EMR or Databricks). This will allow training on the full 100% dataset (11,000,000 rows) without the 12GB RAM Colab bottleneck.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#f28e2b' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>2. Cost-Efficient Storage:</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#f28e2b' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'> Continue utilizing the </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#f28e2b' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Parquet format</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#f28e2b' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'> and </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#f28e2b' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>RDD partitioning</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'> strategy in the cloud. This will minimize I/O overhead and keep enterprise cloud computing costs low.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#f28e2b' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>3. Feature Focus:</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'> Future data collection efforts should prioritize the high-level kinematic features. Dropping the least important low-level features could further reduce processing time and storage costs without sacrificing model accuracy.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
              </zone>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='8' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
          </zones>
        </devicelayout>
      </devicelayouts>
      <simple-id uuid='{3CBBAEDF-19C7-4864-87C0-0EE0A0BDB9B7}' />
    </dashboard>
